<HEAD>Examination and Confe&s;&s;ion of Jack (Comfort's) Before the Grand Jury.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">NUMB. II.</HEAD>
<P>HE repeated much to the &s;ame Purpo&s;e as in his Exami|nation before the Judge;</P>
<Q REND="margQuotes"><P N="1">1. But on repeating over the Per&s;ons who were at <HI>Com|fort'</HI> s Hou&s;e, and <HI>Hugh&s;on'</HI>s, he ob&s;erved, That <HI>Cato,</HI> (COWLEY's) was not at <HI>Hugh&s;on's</HI> at that Meeting; and that <HI>Ben,</HI> and <HI>Qua&s;h,</HI> and <HI>Pablo</HI> [alias <HI>Powlus</HI>] were not at <HI>Comfort'</HI>s at that Meeting; &s;o that the following is a true Li&s;t of each Company, who was there, who are not executed, or indicted.</P></Q>
