<Q REND="margQuotes"><P N="1">1. THAT he was one of the Company at <HI>Hugh&s;on'</HI>s with <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">arcel of Negroes, when <HI>North</HI> the Con|&s;table came, and interrupted them at a Fea&s;t.</P>
<P N="2">2. That on the Sunday following, which was about Whit&s;ontide Twelve Months, <HI>Tom,</HI> belonging to Capta<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">n <HI>Row<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">&punc;</HI> and <HI>Quamin<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">,</HI> belonging to the E&s;tate of <HI>Harris,</HI> in Stone-Street, a&s;ked him, Whether he would do as they would&punc; The Examinant a&s;ked them, what was that? <HI>Old Quamin<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"></HI> an&s;wered, that they would &s;et fire to both Rows of Hou&s;es in Stone-Street, and he would find Powder, and Pi&s;tol and Ball: The Exami|nant &s;aid, he would con&s;ider of it, he did not know whe|ther he would or no: Then <HI>Quamin<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"></HI> pulled out a Razor and threatned to cut his Throat, if he did not agree with them: Upon which he was forced to con&s;ent.</P>
<P N="3">3. That about three Weeks after la&s;t New Year, One Day, about the Middle of the Week, he (the Exami|nant) <HI>Albany,</HI> his Fellow Servant, the abovenamed <HI>Tom,</HI> and the &s;aid <HI>Quamin<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"></HI> were at the Hou&s;e of the &s;aid <HI>John Hugh&s;on,</HI> and had a <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> of Punch, which <HI>Hugh&s;on</HI> brought to them.</P></Q>
