<Q REND="margQuotes"><P N="3">3. That about a Fortnight afterwards, on a Sunday, he went with Pintard's <HI>Cae&s;ar,</HI> in order to meet w<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">h <HI>Albany, Tickle&punc; Curacoa Dick</HI> and Bo&s;ch's <HI>Frank;</HI> and they went down to <HI>Hugh&s;on'</HI>s one after another; when they came there, they went into a Room where were <HI>Hugh&s;on, his wife and Daughter,</HI> but the latter did not &s;tay in the Room; <HI>Hugh&s;on</HI> brought them Drams, which they paid for; and he <HI>talked to them about the Plot for burning the Hou&s;es of the Town, and killing the white People; and told them there were &s;everal Companie<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Negroes to be made up, and a&s;ked if they would be con|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="4 letters">ed?</HI> and &s;ome agreed at that Time; but he and Pintard's <HI>Cae&s;ar</HI> did not, they came out of the Hou&s;e together after &s;taying about Half an Hour.</P>
<P N="4">4. That the Sunday after this, he went to <HI>Hugh&s;on'</HI>s again with <HI>Albany,</HI> and Hugh&s;on <HI>carried</HI> Albany <HI>and him up Stairs, and &s;wore them upon a Bible&punc;</HI> after having told them that there were a great many concerned in this Plot; <HI>that they had agreed to ri&s;e again&s;t the Town, to murder the People; &s;ome to murder their Ma&s;ters and Mi|&s;tre&s;&s;es, and to burn their Hou&s;es; and propo&s;ed to him to do the &s;ame, and de&s;troy the whole Family; which he was unwilling to agree to at fir&s;t; <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> at la&s;t con&s;ented; and then he was &s;worn and ki&s;&s;ed the Book;</HI> and <HI>Albany</HI> con&s;ented to kill his Mi&s;tre&s;s and the re&s;t of the Family, and to burn her Hou&s;e; and was &s;worn in the &s;ame Manner: That the Purpo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters"> of the Oath was, that <HI>they were to keep all &s;ecret, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> to perform what they <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ad &s;everally engaged to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">&punc; and if they failed therein, they were to be damn'd for<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">er.</HI></P>
<P N="5">5. That on another Sunday Evening about a Fort|night or three Weeks after that, he went to a Supper at <HI>Hugh&s;on'</HI>s according to his Invitation.</P></Q>
<P N="6"><Q REND="margQuotes">6. That the la&s;t Time he met Mar&s;chalk's <HI>York</HI> by Mr. <HI>De Lancey'</HI>s, as he was going; when he came there <HI>there were a great Number of Negroes,</HI> he believes <HI>Forty or Fifty,</HI> among which were</Q>
