<HEAD>DEPOSITION.</HEAD>
<P>THIS Day <HI>Stephen Evan</HI> of <HI>We&s;tche&s;ter</HI> County, made Oath before one of the Judges, <Q REND="margQuotes">That being at <HI>Jamaica</HI> on <HI>Long-I&s;land,</HI> about a Year ago, a Negro Man called <HI>Will,</HI> belonging to <HI>Johannes Hardenb<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">gh, Robin</HI> (Ju&s;tice Willet'<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">) and <HI>Jack</HI> (Dorland's) Negroes were at a Hou&s;e where he (the Deponent) was; and that he heard <HI>Will</HI> &s;ay to <HI>Robin, What think you of</HI> Corlaer's Hook<NOTE N="(n)" PLACE="foot"><HI>A Point of Land at the Ea&s;t End of the City of</HI> New-York, <HI>almo&s;t oppo&s;ite</HI> Long-I&s;land <HI>Ferry</HI></NOTE> <HI>or of the Plot? D&mdash;n it,</HI> replied Robin, <HI>I'll have nothing to &s;ay to it; if they burn their Back&s;ides, they mu&s;t &s;it down on the Bli&s;t<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">rs;</HI> but &s;aid further, <HI>Let them go on and pro&s;per.</HI></Q></P>
<P><PB N="92" REF="005413_0100_10173A5D5C0A1DA8">
<Q REND="margQuotes">That this Deponent urged very hard to know what they meant; one of them (he thought it was <HI>Robin</HI>) &s;aid, <HI>it was a Plot; and that if it went <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">n, he</HI> (the Deponent) <HI>&s;hould hear more of it, and could do no le&s;s than hear of it; but would then &s;ay no more about i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> for fear of bringing him&s;elf in.</HI></Q></P>
