<P><HI>YORK</HI> (Thomp&s;on's) <HI>&s;aid.</HI> <Q REND="margQuotes">That &s;ome time la&s;t Winter, Furman's <HI>Harry</HI> carried him to <HI>Hugh&s;on'</HI>s with Woolf's <HI>Dick,</HI> and told the Pri&s;oner of the Plot, and not to tell any Body; That <HI>London</HI> (A. Van Horn's) was told by the Pri&s;oner of the Plot, and he agreed to be one: There were pre&s;ent at the &s;ame Time at <HI>Hugh&s;on'</HI>s, be&s;ides the before-mentioned; <HI>Jack,</HI> Comfort's, and <HI>Warwick,</HI> Hunt's.</Q></P>
