<CELL>&sect;5.</CELL>
<CELL><HI>pa.</HI> 97.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL><HI>Dick</HI> (Ten Eyck's) Confe&s;&s;ion,</CELL>
<CELL>&nbsp;</CELL>
<CELL>30<HI>th June</HI></CELL>
</ROW>
</TABLE></P>
</DIV1>
</BODY>
</TEXT></Q>
<P>This Day the following Negroes were apprehended and committed; <HI>Venture,</HI> Tiebout'<HI>s; Jack,</HI> Abraham&s;e's; <HI>Fortune,</HI> Capt. Walton's; <HI>Jack,</HI> Roerback's.</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="day">
<HEAD>Supreme Court: MONDAY, 29th JUNE.</HEAD>
<P>PRESENT, The Second and Third Justices.</P>
<P>The KING, <HI>again&s;t</HI>
<LIST>
<HEAD>Negroes.</HEAD>
<ITEM>Jack, DORLAND's</ITEM>
<ITEM>Will, HARDENBERGH's</ITEM>
</LIST></P>
<P><HI>JOHN DORLAND</HI> and <HI>Johannes Hardenbergh</HI> entered into Recognizance for the Appearance of <HI>Jack</HI> and <HI>Will,</HI> two Negroes, at the next Court of Oyer and Terminer and General Goal Delivery for <HI>Queens</HI> County, thereon <HI>Ordered,</HI> That the Sheriff of <HI>Queens</HI> County do di&s;charge out of his Cu&s;tody the &s;aid Negroes.<NOTE N="(r)" PLACE="foot"><HI>See Depo&s;ition of</HI> Stephen Evan, <HI>page</HI> 91.</NOTE></P>
<P><PB N="113" REF="005413_0121_10173AA0EA825300">
His Maje&s;ty's ORDINANCE for the further Enlarging the pre&s;ent Term until Saturday the 25th Day of <HI>July</HI> next, publi&s;hed.</P>
