<P><HI>FORTUNE</HI> (Mr. D. Clark&s;on's) <HI>&s;aid,</HI> <Q REND="margQuotes">That &s;ome time about Chri&s;tma&s;s la&s;t, he was going to <HI>Com|fort'</HI>s for Tea-Water, where he &s;aw <HI>Ben.</HI> (Capt. Mar&s;hall's) <HI>Qua&s;h</HI> (Mr. Rutgers's) and <HI>Fortune</HI> (Mr. Vander&s;p<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">gle's) on the Hill at <HI>Comfort'</HI>s; that they carried him to <HI>Hugh&s;on'</HI>s, where they had one or two Bowls of Punch; that <HI>Hugh&s;on</HI> drank with them and told them they &s;hould never want for Liquor whether they had Money or not;
