<P><HI>CAESAR</HI>(Kortrecht's) <HI>&s;aid,</HI> <Q REND="margQuotes">That la&s;t Chri&s;tma&s;s he went with <HI>Jack</HI> (Comfort's) to <HI>Hugh&s;on'</HI>s; that he was in the Shop, and much in Liquor; that he &s;aw <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> <HI>Room full of Negroes</HI> eating and drinking, but does not know who they were, being the whole Time in the Shop; that Comfort's <HI>Jack</HI> coming out with the Pri&s;oner told him, <HI>the</HI> Spaniards <HI>were coming here, and that the Negroes were going to ri&s;e, and would help the Spaniards;</HI> that he offered him <HI>(Cae&s;ar)</HI> a Knife to fight with again&s;t the white People; but he refu&s;ed it, having one in his Pocket; That then <HI>Jack &s;wore him</HI> to be one among them, and he promi&s;ed them he would.</Q></P>
