<P><HI>SAM</HI> (Lowe's) <HI>&s;aid,</HI> <Q REND="margQuotes">That <HI>on Ea&s;ter Hollidays was a Year,</HI> he went to <HI>Hugh&s;on'</HI>s with Comfort's <HI>Jack,</HI> where he &s;aw Mr. Philip&s;e's <HI>Frank</HI> and Hyer's <HI>Tom&punc;</HI> that <HI>Frank</HI> was drinking Beer; that <HI>Hugh&s;on</HI> carried him into ano|ther Room, and a&s;ked him <HI>if he would be concerned with him in taking the Town?</HI> he &s;aid he would, if it could be done; that <HI>Hugh&s;on</HI> told him it could; <HI>and then he &s;wore him, and told him, that when the Hou&s;es were on fire, he</HI> &s;hould come to him, and he would furni&s;h him with Arms.</Q></P>
