<ITEM>Tom, LIVINGSTON's.</ITEM>
<ITEM>Tickle, CARPENTER's.</ITEM>
<ITEM>Sandy, NIBBLET's</ITEM>
</LIST></P>
<P>THE Pri&s;oners having been indicted for the Con&s;piracy, were &s;et to the Bar, and arraigned, and all of them pleaded, <HI>GUILTY</HI> to the Indictment.</P>
<P>THE KING, <HI>again&s;t</HI> Billy, ELLISTON's <HI>Negro.</HI></P>
<P>PROCLAMATION having been made, and none appearing to pro&s;ecute, the Pri&s;oner was di&s;charged.</P>
<LIST>
<HEAD>The KING again&s;t Eighteen NEGROES. viz.</HEAD>
<ITEM><HI>Jack,</HI>  Slydal's.</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Sandy,</HI>  Nibblet's.</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Tickle,</HI>  Carpenters.</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Low,</HI>  Dav. Provo&s;t's.</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Jeffery,</HI>  J. Brown's.</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Sam,</HI>  Peter Lowe's.</ITEM>
<ITEM><LIST>
<ITEM><HI>Jack,</HI></ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Adam,</HI></ITEM>
</LIST> Murray's.</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Toby,</HI>  Wendover's.</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Jack,</HI>  Brea&s;ted's.</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Cae&s;ar,</HI>  Horsfield's.</ITEM>
